To install the Rohingya Hanifi keyboard layout for Linux:

1. Run the following command to install IBus and the m17n module:

  sudo apt-get install ibus-m17n

2. Run the following command to enable IBus as the default input method:

  im-config -n ibus

3. Log out and log back in to your system. You should now have a small language switcher icon near the time at the top of your screen.

4. Download rhg-hanifi.mim and place it into your usr/share/m17n/ directory.

5. Right-click on the language switcher icon and select "Preferences."

6. Navigate to the "Input Method" tab and click "Add."

7. Click the three dots at the bottom of the list to expand the language selection, then scroll down and click "other."

8. Select "hanifi (m17n)" and click "Add."

You should now be able to select "Other - hanifi (m17n)" when you click on the language switcher.
